alerts.title: Winter Storm Warning
alerts.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 10 PM EST FRIDAY... * WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 8 to 12 inches with 12 to 18 inches over the southern Greens. * WHERE...The western and southern Adirondacks, Lake George Saratoga region, and southern Vermont. * WHEN...From 1 AM to 10 PM EST Friday. * IMPACTS...Travel will be very difficult to impossible. The hazardous conditions will impact the morning commute and may impact the evening commute Friday. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Maximum snowfall rates of 1 to 2 inches per hour are expected in the morning prior to daybreak and may continue into the early afternoon.
